Irish Brown Soda Bread
  --Cook's Illustrated
  
2 c (11 oz) whole wheat flour
1 c (5 oz) ap flour
1 c wheat bran
1/4 c wheat germ
2 tsp sugar
1 1/2 tsp baking powder
1 1/2 tsp baking soda
1 tsp salt
2 c buttermilk

Adjust oven rack to middle position and heat oven to 375F. Lightly grease 8" round cake pan. Whisk flours, bran, germ, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, and salt together in medium bowl. Add buttermilk and stir with rubber spatula until all flour is moistened and dough forms soft, ragged mass. Transfer dough to workarea and gently shape into 6" round. Using serrated knife, cut 1/2" deep cross ~5" long on top of loaf. Transfer to prepared pan. Bake until loaf is lightly browned and center registers 185F, 40-45 min, rotating pan halfway through baking. Invert onto wire rack. Reinvert loafand cool for at least 1 hr. Slice and serve.


Notes: leftovers can be wrapped in plastic and stored for up to 2 days.
